<div id="overviewBlock">
	<h3>Overview:</h3>
	<p>A plethora of Far Right and fascist organizations emerged in the wake of World War I. Economic depression, nationalism, anti-Semitism and xenophobia all played a part in this upsurge. On the left, the tension between communist revolutionaries and socialist reformers was reconciled, for a time, in the Popular Front government of Leon Blum. While the Popular Front would eventually fall, it pioneered many of the reforms and progressive measures that French workers enjoy today.</p>
</div>
<div id="readingBlock">
	<h3>Reading assignment:</h3>
	<p>Sowerwine, Charles. <em>France since 1870: Culture, Politics and Society</em>, pp. 121-192.</p>
	<p>Bloch, Marc. <em>Strange Defeat</em>. </p>
</div>
